Add an AArch64 case to the darwin hosted flavour in AROS's configure(.in).

Context: in configure the `darwin*)` target_os branch switches over `$target_cpu`
for i386 / x86_64 / ppc / arm, then errors on anything else:

        *)
            as_fn_error $? "\"Unsupported target CPU for darwin hosted flavour -- $target_cpu\"" "$LINENO" 5
            ;;

Insert this case BEFORE that default `*)`. Modelled on the existing *x86_64* and
*arm* cases, but uses the NATIVE Apple-Silicon toolchain (clang -arch arm64 via the
llvm toolchain family) instead of a dead `*-apple-darwin10-` cross-prefix.

            *aarch64*|*arm64*)
                PLATFORM_EXECSMP="#define __AROSPLATFORM_SMP__"
                aros_target_cpu="aarch64"
                aros_object_format="aarch64elf_aros"
                aros_target_mkdep="$aros_target_mkdep -D__GNUC__ -Daarch64"
                aros_macosx_version="11.0"          # first macOS on Apple Silicon
                aros_config_cflags="$aros_config_cflags $""(CFLAGS_NO_OMIT_FP)"
                aros_config_cxxflags="$aros_config_cxxflags $""(CFLAGS_NO_OMIT_FP)"
                aros_kernel_isa_flags="-arch arm64"
                aros_kernel_ldflags="-arch arm64"
                aros_nominal_depth=8
                aros_kernel_rs="$toolchain_ar"
                aros_kernel_ar_flags="-cr"
                aros_kernel_ld="$toolchain_ld -arch arm64"
                aros_kernel_as="$toolchain_as -arch arm64"
                aros_kernel_ranlib="ranlib"
                aros_kernel_nm="nm"
                aros_kernel_strip="strip"
                # Native toolchain, not a darwin10 cross-prefix:
                kernel_tool_prefix=""
                llvm_target_cpu="AArch64"
                ;;

Notes / still-to-resolve (the integration, not research):
  - Confirm the binutils/lld emulation name for the object format on darwin-arm64
    (`aarch64elf_aros` mirrors the arm `armelf_aros`; the hosted Mach-O link may
    instead want the native ld with -arch arm64 and no -m <emul>).
  - This pairs with: graft/cpu_aarch64.h (arch/all-darwin/kernel/) and
    graft/cpucontext-aarch64.h (arch/aarch64-all/include/aros/).
  - Drive `--with-toolchain=llvm` so AROS uses clang/lld; the darwin10 iPhone
    SDK paths in the other cases must NOT be inherited.
